videos.description: Aaron Epps gets the pass in the corner and fools his defender with the pump fake leading to a wide-open three in the corner.
videos.headline: Epps drills 3-pointer to extend Tigers' lead into half

videos.description: PJ Washington gets the feed down low and towers over the defender for the one-handed throw down.
videos.headline: Washington shakes the rim with one-handed jam

videos.description: PJ Washington swats away the Tigers' shot resulting in a turnover in favor of the Wildcats.
videos.headline: Washington is a new resident of block city

videos.description: Duop Reath hits the open three from the top of the arc to give the Tigers the advantage over Kentucky.
videos.headline: Reath three gives LSU the lead

videos.description: Duop Reath gets the feed underneath and jams it home to keep the Tigers right in it with No. 17 Kentucky.
videos.headline: Reath shakes the rim to tie game

videos.description: LSU looks to Brandon Sampson for the last shot, but his 3-point attempt hits the front of the rim and bounces out giving Kentucky the win.
videos.headline: Kentucky survives as LSU's final shot just misses

videos.description: No. 17 Kentucky uses strong performances from PJ Washington and Kevin Knox to pull out the close win against LSU.
videos.headline: Kentucky fights off LSU in a hard-fought victory

videos.description: LSU's Brandon Sampson bricks a 3-pointer as time expires to finish Kentucky's 74-71 victory on the road.
videos.headline: Kentucky escapes against LSU
